My family and I have been long time regular customers of Pasta Brioni, and we are definite fans, but...
I come from a large New York-Italian family, so I am definitely picky about my Italian food, and generally speaking, PB makes the cut.
I must say however, that since ownership changed (Think it was from father to son) the quality of food and service has definitely changed for the worse.
Back when the old man was running the place, it would have received 5 stars from me, now it *only* gets 4 stars.
As for the food, it is always hot, and always delicious.
There are many specialty items that are not on the menu or specials board, so if you want something specific but don't see it, ask.
There's a good chance they can make it for you.
Portions are usually more than we can eat, and they make outstanding midnight snacks.
As someone else said, the waiters are all "Italian Stallions", but that's part of the attraction for the ladies (They even have a calendar featuring the waiters).
In my experience, the service is very good.
Your glass is never empty and the food is served pretty quickly.
You're checked on several times throughout the course of the meal to see if you need anything else.
The part of the restaurant that still gets 5 stars in my opinion, is the take-out side.
The pizza is authentic NYC Pizza (better than anywhere else in AZ), and the Eggplant Parmesan is the best I've ever had from a restaurant.
Generous side salads come with every meal and are delicious.

