The person I spoke with mentioned that they would have a special table ready for her and a cake.
When we arrived, we were instructed to pick our own table; no special preparations.
Had to ask multiple times for the parmesan cheese which, when finally brought out, was in a grinder that kept breaking on the waiter.
At the completion of the meal that waiter asked, "done yet"?
How about, "ma'm are you finished yet"?
The olive oil was rancid.
For the price of lunch ($74 for two), will not be back.

