A must try!

Mama Mia...what a hero.
Discovered this place while shopping at Sprouts.
It is visible, but kind of tucked away.
The cafe entrance is around the back and they offer takeout and all the usual Italian items.
My choice was one of the better chicken parmesan hero's (or grinders (which is a Connecticut thing) as they call it here).
This was a sandwich loaded with cutlets, a tasty sauce and just enough melted cheese.
The bread wasn't a sesame seed roll, but was more fancy, but I do not know the bread name.
It was $8.25 and came with a side of pretty good pasta salad, that was a bit garlicky.
Next time, they need to separate the cold pasta from the hot hero because the salad ended up hot as I returned to the crib.
Overall, this was probably the best chicken parm I have had in the valley.

